&lt;p&gt;The Transfer Pricing team is a strategic partner to the business, responsible for designing, implementing, and managing the company’s global transfer pricing framework across a rapidly growing multinational technology organization. The team supports business expansion, acquisitions, operating model evolution, intellectual property management, and global tax compliance while ensuring alignment with OECD Transfer Pricing Guidelines and local country requirements. Working closely with Finance, Accounting, Legal, Corporate Development, and business leaders, the team helps enable scalable growth through data-driven decision making, operational excellence, and proactive risk management. Team members gain exposure to complex cross-border transactions, post-acquisition integrations, tax authority audits, and global transformation initiatives, while partnering with stakeholders across North America, EMEA, and APAC. This is a highly visible team that plays a critical role in supporting the company’s continued growth and innovation on a global scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Transfer Pricing Manager will lead the development, execution, and defense of global transfer pricing strategies. This role requires deep technical expertise and leadership capability across multiple jurisdictions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re excited about this opportunity because you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement global transfer pricing policies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee TP documentation (Master File, Local Files, CbCR)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical leadership on OECD, IRC 482, UK TIOPA, Finnish TP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage audits and controversy matters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead economic analyses and benchmarking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with cross-functional teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor junior staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re excited about you because…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7–12 years of transfer pricing experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong expertise in OECD, IRC 482, UK TIOPA, Finnish TP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leadership and project management experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in multinational environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About DoorDash&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At DoorDash, our mission to empower local economies shapes how our team members move quickly, learn, and reiterate in order to make impactful decisions that display empathy for our range of users—from Dashers to merchant partners to consumers. We are a technology and logistics company that started by enabling door-to-door delivery, and we are looking for team members who can help us go from a company that is known as the place you order food to a company that people turn to for any and all goods.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;DoorDash is growing rapidly and changing constantly, which gives our team members the opportunity to share their unique perspectives, solve new challenges, and own their careers. We&#39;re committed to supporting employees’ happiness, healthiness, and overall well-being by providing comprehensive benefits and perks.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Commitment to Diversity and

