&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dedicated Workday Integrations Specialist to join our People Tech team. This role involves crafting and managing integrations within Workday, enhancing system functionality, and providing essential support to our business operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Integration Development and Management:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with stakeholders to understand integration needs and objectives.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement robust integration solutions connecting Workday with internal and external systems using tools such as Workday Studio, EIB, and Core Connectors, Picof/ PECI&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the accuracy, efficiency, and security of data through comprehensive testing and error management.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide ongoing support and maintenance for existing integrations, serving as the primary technical contact for business teams.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document all integration processes and maintain a detailed log of system changes and updates.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System Configuration and Enhancement:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop custom Workday Extend applications by working closely with business stakeholders to meet their needs.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recommend and implement improvements and innovations within the Workday platform.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the integration aspects of Workday system upgrades, ensuring compatibility and functionality with new releases.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compliance and Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work alongside the HR team to ensure system security, business process compliance, and alignment with audit requirements such as SOC and SOX.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage with the broader Workday community to stay abreast of new technologies and best practices, using this knowledge to propose solutions that address business challenges.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project and Implementation Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead Workday integration projects from conception through to successful execution, ensuring alignment with the overall People Tech roadmap.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the implementation of system configurations, testing, training, and deployment to enhance user adoption and satisfaction.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Humble Expectations&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
